2026-06-23T22:25:55.959392+01:00 INFO GET path=/api/projects/3/tickets status=200 duration_ms=2 request_id=50b4446e-c963-47c4-8409-52251d6f49b2 response_body="[{\"ticket_id\":\"TK-129\",\"project_id\":3,\"type\":\"task\",\"title\":\"tk invite \\u003cemail, username\\u003e -project P -role R - to send an ingite to a user to join a project in a role.  Whic actually puts them into a team, which is the team of users in that project.\",\"description\":\"\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"\",\"git_repository\":\"\",\"git_branch\":\"\",\"workflow_stage_id\":1,\"role_id\":14,\"stage\":\"design\",\"state\":\"idle\",\"status\":\"design/idle\",\"priority\":1,\"order\":0,\"estimate_effort\":0,\"health_score\":0,\"assignee\":\"\",\"author\":\"admin\",\"draft\":true,\"complete\":false,\"archived\":false,\"deleted\":false,\"recommended_ready\":false,\"created_by\":\"eadacd03-7812-40fb-9bb4-8a018ae41aa9\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-23 19:19:09\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-23 19:19:09\"},{\"ticket_id\":\"TK-128\",\"project_id\":3,\"type\":\"task\",\"title\":\"the arrow keys and wasd are not working in the backlog to control the focus; rather they scroll the whole area.\",\"description\":\"\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"\",\"git_repository\":\"\",\"git_branch\":\"\",\"workflow_stage_id\":1,\"role_id\":14,\"stage\":\"design\",\"state\":\"idle\",\"status\":\"design/idle\",\"priority\":1,\"order\":0,\"estimate_effort\":0,\"health_score\":0,\"assignee\":\"\",\"author\":\"admin\",\"draft\":true,\"complete\":false,\"archived\":false,\"deleted\":false,\"recommended_ready\":false,\"created_by\":\"eadacd03-7812-40fb-9bb4-8a018ae41aa9\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-23 19:16:48\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-23 19:16:48\"},{\"ticket_id\":\"TK-100\",\"project_id\":3,\"parent_id\":\"TK-94\",\"type\":\"story\",\"title\":\"S6 cmd/tk-website BFF binary + docker image\",\"description\":\"Add cmd/tk-website: a standalone binary that serves the embedded frontend assets AND reverse-proxies /api to a configured tk-server (BFF, same-origin, no CORS).\\n- Backend URL configured server-side (env/flag).\\n- Provide a Dockerfile and publish a ghcr.io/simonski/tk-website image.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"1. tk-website serves the SPA and proxies /api to the configured tk-server.\\n2. No CORS needed (same-origin).\\n3. Backend URL is configurable.\\n4. Dockerfile builds and an image publishes to ghcr.io.\\n5. A browser smoke test passes against tk-website + tk-server.\",\"ac_map\":{\"default\":\"1. tk-website serves the SPA and proxies /api to the configured tk-server.\\n2. No CORS needed (same-origin).\\n3. Backend URL is configurable.\\n4. Dockerfile builds and an image publishes to ghcr.io.\\n5. A browser smoke test passes against tk-website + tk-server.\"},\"git_repository\":\"\",\"git_branch\":\"\",\"workflow_stage_id\":1,\"role_id\":14,\"stage\":\"design\",\"state\":\"idle\",\"status\":\"design/idle\",\"priority\":1,\"order\":0,\"estimate_effort\":0,\"health_score\":0,\"assignee\":\"\",\"author\":\"admin\",\"draft\":true,\"complete\":false,\"archived\":false,\"deleted\":false,\"recommended_ready\":false,\"created_by\":\"eadacd03-7812-40fb-9bb4-8a018ae41aa9\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-22 21:39:47\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-22 21:39:47\"},{\"ticket_id\":\"TK-101\",\"project_id\":3,\"parent_id\":\"TK-94\",\"type\":\"story\",\"title\":\"S7 Rewire unified tk to compose the libraries\",\"description\":\"Rewire cmd/tk to compose server + cli + website in-process using the new libraries, proving the decomposition end-to-end.\\n- tk provides the local-capable, all-in-one experience (server-less local use, embedded web, CLI/TUI).\\n- No duplicated logic: tk imports the same libs the component binaries use.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"1. tk composes server+webui+cli from the shared libraries (no forked logic).\\n2. tk works fully offline/local.\\n3. tk passes test-all.\\n4. The four binaries share one source tree and the same contract version.\",\"ac_map\":{\"default\":\"1. tk composes server+webui+cli from the shared libraries (no forked logic).\\n2. tk works fully offline/local.\\n3. tk passes test-all.\\n4. The four binaries share one source tree and the same contract version.\"},\"git_repository\":\"\",\"git_branch\":\"\",\"workflow_stage_id\":1,\"role_id\":14,\"stage\":\"design\",\"state\":\"idle\",\"status\":\"design/idle\",\"priority\":1,\"order\":0,\"estimate_effort\":0,\"health_score\":0,\"assignee\":\"\",\"author\":\"admin\",\"draft\":true,\"complete\":false,\"archived\":false,\"deleted\":false,\"recommended_ready\":false,\"created_by\":\"eadacd03-7812-40fb-9bb4-8a018ae41aa9\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06…(truncated)"
2026-06-23T22:25:55.963913+01:00 INFO GET path=/api/tickets/TK-94 status=200 duration_ms=1 request_id=18f27a03-aa16-4d82-a60e-68f705cb4dff response_body="{\"ticket_id\":\"TK-94\",\"project_id\":3,\"type\":\"epic\",\"title\":\"Split the single tk binary into independently-releasable components behind an API contract version\",\"description\":\"Split the current single Go binary (cmd/tk) into independently-releasable components that obey a versioned API contract, while preserving a unified tk binary buildable from one git clone.\\n\\nComponents (artefacts):\\n- tk          unified, local-capable single binary (all-in-one)\\n- tk-cli      thin, remote-only CLI + TUI (no embedded store)\\n- tk-server   API + DB (SQLite); standalone binary AND ghcr.io docker image\\n- tk-website  frontend assets + BFF reverse-proxy to tk-server; standalone binary AND docker image\\n\\nTwo version axes:\\n- Component version: each artefact carries its own release version (drives CI, brew, docker tags).\\n- API contract version: a single major.minor.patch in docs/api/openapi.yaml, embedded in client and server, advertised by GET /api/status and checked at a startup handshake. Compatibility rule: reject on MAJOR mismatch; accept differing MINOR/PATCH (standard semver).\\n\\nLibrary decomposition: store, server (an http.Handler mounting the contract over a libticket.Service), libticket (the SDK: Service interface + LocalService + HTTPService), and webui (embedded assets) become clean importable packages. Binaries are thin main() wrappers. The existing libticket contract tests remain the cross-implementation guarantee.\\n\\nDeveloper experience: make build-all/test-all produce and verify the unified tk and all components; per-component build-\\u003cc\\u003e/test-\\u003cc\\u003e allow selective build/test/release. tk compose emits a docker-compose.yml pinning ghcr images. brew install tk and brew install tk-server install the artefacts.\\n\\nMotivation: selectively test and release components instead of the whole project, while remaining able to assemble everything into one convenient binary.\\n\\nGit workflow: this epic lives on branch epic/component-split (off main). Each story branches off the epic branch with its own PR into the epic; the epic merges to main only once all stories are complete. Design and documentation (S1) land first, before any implementation.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"1. Design docs + diagrams (S1) are reviewed and merged onto the epic branch before any implementation code.\\n2. Unified tk still builds and passes make test-all.\\n3. tk-cli, tk-server, tk-website each build, test, and release as independent artefacts.\\n4. The API contract version is embedded in client+server; the startup handshake rejects a MAJOR mismatch with a clear message while accepting MINOR/PATCH differences.\\n5. tk-server and tk-website publish docker images to ghcr.io; brew formulae exist for tk and tk-server.\\n6. tk compose emits a valid docker-compose.yml that runs tk-server + tk-website.\\n7. make build-all/test-all and per-component build-*/test-* targets exist and pass in CI.\\n8. All stories are complete and the epic branch is merged to main as a single feature.\",\"ac_map\":{\"default\":\"1. Design docs + diagrams (S1) are reviewed and merged onto the epic branch before any implementation code.\\n2. Unified tk still builds and passes make test-all.\\n3. tk-cli, tk-server, tk-website each build, test, and release as independent artefacts.\\n4. The API contract version is embedded in client+server; the startup handshake rejects a MAJOR mismatch with a clear message while accepting MINOR/PATCH differences.\\n5. tk-server and tk-website publish docker images to ghcr.io; brew formulae exist for tk and tk-server.\\n6. tk compose emits a valid docker-compose.yml that runs tk-server + tk-website.\\n7. make build-all/test-all and per-component build-*/test-* targets exist and pass in CI.\\n8. All stories are complete and the epic branch is merged to main as a single feature.\"},\"git_repository\":\"\",\"git_branch\":\"\",\"workflow_stage_id\":1,\"role_id\":14,\"stage\":\"design\",\"state\":\"idle\",\"status\":\"design/idle\",\"priority\":1,\"order\":0,\"estimate_effort\":0,\"health_score\":0,\"assignee\":\"\",\"author\":\"admin\",\"draft\":true,\"complete\":false,\"archived\":false,\"deleted\":false,\"recommen…(truncated)"
